		<div class="comment-body"><p>If anyone&#8217;s paying down/off their credit card, take a moment to look at the statements (I&#8217;m sure most of us do).  My wife and I just paid off a bank of america card in order to cancel it.  We received their statement yesterday stating we owed $4.61.  I looked at the itemized stuff towards the bottom and it showed our balance as $0.00 on Aug 22.  Three days later on Aug 25 it showed a $4.61 interest charge.</p>
<p>Unless I read it wrong, bank of america charges a hell of a lot of interest to keep a zero dollar balance for three days.</p>
<p>My wife phoned them immediately and politely asked them to waive the charge and they did so right away.</p>
<p>Keep your eyes peeled when you mess with these entities please.</p>
