		<div class="comment-body"><p>I kind of wish you would get off the Colorado water &#8220;oppression&#8221; thing. Denver gets around 12&#8243; of rain a year, at this rate you&#8217;d fill the 2&#215;96 gallon stealth rain barrels in maybe 10 years? Rain barrels are just not worth the effort here. Better to do as you suggest &#8211; store the rainfall (which can be torrential at times) in the ground. My swales here have done me well so far, but it&#8217;s now entering another hot and very dry spell for me. Interestingly, the water laws came about as a <i>protection</i> for the &#8220;little guy&#8221;, as &#8220;first in time, first in right&#8221; prevented a big mine owner from coming along after the homesteader and diverting their stream.</p>
